{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a jug onto mixing bowl lid, weigh olive oil into jug and set aside.","Place bread into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>.","Add red peppers, garlic, walnuts, pomegranate molasses, lemon juice, cumin, paprika, cayenne pepper, Aleppo pepper flakes and salt and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b> to obtain a sauce of chunky texture (see tip). Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and adjust seasoning to taste.","Mix <b>1 min 30 sec\/speed 4<b> while very slowly pouring reserved olive oil onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle around measuring cup in a thin stream onto rotating blades. Transfer muhamara dip into a serving bowl, drizzle with a bit of olive oil and garnish with fresh parsley or mint leaves."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for drizzling","40 g bread, in pieces","350 g red pointed peppers, roasted, cut into pieces, skin and seeds removed (see tip)","2 - 4 garlic cloves","75 g shelled walnuts","2 tbsp pomegranate molasses","1 tsp lemon juice, freshly squeezed, adjust to taste","½ tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground paprika","¼ tsp ground cayenne pepper","1 tsp Aleppo pepper flakes              (optional)","½ tsp salt, adjust to taste","fresh parsley or mint leaves, to garnish"]}],"id":"r168210","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-o0hkui2WXsU\/XZaqwAJiB7I\/AAAAAAAAhgc\/08vdFTI6k_MDiNn_m9q7NPLWozK6H9_qACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lS1oqmod8Hn_y_H5.png","title":"Muhamara dip","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"18.1 g","fat":"172.6 g","uom":"per 1 Complete recipe","carbohydrates":"65 g","calories":"7891 kJ \/ 1886 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jug, serving bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Roasted or chargrilled vegetables have an intense flavour. <br><strong>Grilling over a gas burner:<\/strong> turn the burner to high heat and hold a pepper with tongs over the flame turning occasionally until all sides are charred and the peppers are soft. <br><strong>Grilling in the oven:<\/strong> preheat the oven to 200°C  and grill peppers turning occasionally until all sides are charred and the flesh is soft. <br>Remove from the heat and transfer to a sealable heat resistant plastic bag, seal and leave to rest for <b>10 minutes<b> then peel off the skin and any charred edges.","If you prefer a smoother texture at the end of <b>step 3<b> blend <strong>20 sec\/speed 9<\/strong>.","This sauce can be served as a dip with pitta bread, spread on flatbreads, mixed into stews or served with pasta or potatoes, in which case you can omit the bread crumbs."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","5m","1"]}